</form><html xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:math="java.lang.Math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions" xmlns:xdt="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-datatypes" xmlns:caml="http://lc.ca.gov/legalservices/schemas/caml.1#" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><title>AB2596:v98#DOCUMENT</title><meta name="dc:identifier" content="AB2596"/><meta name="dc:title" content="AB &#xA;              2596-&#xA;                AMENDED&#xA;              "/><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html;charset=utf-8"/></head><body><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Start</h2></span><div id="bill_all" align="justify"><div id="about"><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td align="center"><span style=" text-transform: uppercase; font-size: 1em">
                Amended
               IN </span><span style=" text-transform: uppercase; font-size: 1em">
                Senate
              </span> <span style="text-transform: uppercase">June 18, 2026</span><br/></td></tr></tbody><tbody><tr><td align="center"/></tr></tbody></table></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><font size="3" style="FONT-FAMILY: MinionPC, Arial Unicode MS">
                    CALIFORNIA LEGISLATURE—
                    2025–2026 REGULAR SESSION</font></div><br clear="all"/><span id="bill_house_num"><div style="float: left; width:50%; font-weight: bold; "><span style="text-transform: uppercase; text-align:left;width:50%;"><b>
                Assembly Bill
              </b></span></div><div style="float:right; width:50%; text-align:right;"><span style="text-transform: uppercase;"><b>No. 2596</b></span></div></span><hr/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td id="bill_authors" align="center"><span style="font-weight:bold;">Introduced by Assembly Member Gipson<br/><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>(Coauthor: Senator Cabaldon)<br/></i></font></span></td></tr><tr><td id="bill_intro_date" align="center" class="textcenter"><br/>February 20, 2026</td></tr></tbody></table></div><hr/><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> An act to add Section 798.14.5 to the Civil Code, relating to housing. </span></div><br clear="all"/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">AB 2596, as amended, Gipson.
                          Mobilehome parks: federally approved housing programs: compliance with state and local laws.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Existing law, the Mobilehome Residency Law, prescribes various terms and conditions of tenancies in mobilehome parks.<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> Existing law authorizes a local agency to be responsible for the enforcement of certain requirements governing mobilehome parks.</i></font></div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This bill would specify that,<font color="#B30000"><strike> if</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> in the event that</i></font> a mobilehome park<font color="#B30000"><strike> operator or owner</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> operator, owner, or management</i></font>
			 fails<font color="#B30000"><strike> to</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> to, or elects not to,</i></font> comply with federal law or other federal requirements imposed in connection with a federally approved housing program, the mobilehome park<font color="#B30000"><strike> operator or owner</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> operator, owner, or management</i></font> shall ensure ongoing compliance with<font color="#B30000"><strike> applicable state
			 laws, including, but not limited to,</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> the Mobilehome Residency Law, the</i></font> prescribed provisions of the Unruh Civil Rights Act, and<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> all other applicable state and</i></font> local<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> laws and</i></font> ordinances.<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> If a mobilehome park operator, owner, or management fails to, or elects not to, conduct the age verification requirement under prescribed federal law, the bill would authorize a local agency to conduct age verification, as provided, and grant the local agency with the right to access and inspect records of the mobilehome park operator, owner, and management to conduct that verification.</i></font></div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="vote">
      Vote:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">MAJORITY</span>  </span><span id="appropriation">
      Appropriation:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span><span id="localprogram">
      Local Program:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><div id="bill"><div style=" text-transform: uppercase"><h2 style=" text-align: left;">The people of the State of California do enact as follows:</h2><br/></div><div id="s10.12306503860336815"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0" class="ActionLine"><h3 style="font-weight:bold; display:inline;">SECTION 1.</h3> Section 798.14.5 is added to the Civil Code, to read:</div><div><font color="#B30000"><strike><caml:LawSection id="id_11CA4243-1E17-4A94-A6EC-FFBBEAC2BC2C"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>798.14.5.</caml:Num><caml:LawSectionVersion id="id_FAE5D86E-B87E-4900-9CEF-DCA815F0D6C0"><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>If</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:LawSectionVersion></caml:LawSection></strike></font><div id="id_2D1A21D0-BF2C-4DB4-963D-C10157145F31"><div><p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h6 style="display:inline;"><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>798.14.5.</i></font></h6> <font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>(a)</i></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> In the event that</i></font> a mobilehome park<font color="#B30000"><strike> operator or owner</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> operator, owner, or management</i></font> fails<font color="#B30000"><strike> to</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> to, or elects not to,</i></font>comply with federal law or other federal requirements imposed in connection with a federally approved housing program,<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> including, but not limited to, the Housing for Older Persons Act of 1995,</i></font> the mobilehome park<font color="#B30000"><strike> operator or owner</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> operator, owner, or management</i></font> shall ensure ongoing compliance with<font color="#B30000"><strike> applicable state laws, including, but not limited to,</strike></font> this chapter, Sections 51.2 and 51.3, and<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> applicable state and</i></font> local<font color="#B30000"><strike>						ordinances.</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>
						laws and ordinances, including those regulating or requiring operation as a senior mobilehome park, or which define a mobilehome park or a senior mobilehome park under state or local laws.</i></font></div><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(b) In the event that a mobilehome park operator, owner, or management fails or elects not to conduct the age verification requirement under the Housing for Older Persons Act of 1995, a local agency may conduct the age verification by any means authorized by law, and shall have the right to access and inspect records of the mobilehome park operator, owner, and management to conduct the verification.</div></i></font></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></body></html>
